1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,384 --> 00:01:37,867
=Episode 6=
(Mom)

3
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:40,267
(2023, Qidaohezi)

4
00:01:40,267 --> 00:01:41,627
Why did you ask about Ms. Zhou?

5
00:01:42,146 --> 00:01:43,267
Is it about your case?

6
00:01:43,267 --> 00:01:46,187
Hold on. We have rules.
We can't discuss that.

7
00:01:46,946 --> 00:01:49,706
Okay, then don't say what you shouldn't.

8
00:01:50,547 --> 00:01:54,866
But what you wanted to ask
wasn't about Ms. Zhou, was it?

9
00:01:55,346 --> 00:01:56,107
Then what was it?

10
00:01:58,506 --> 00:02:00,066
Ask when you actually want to know.

11
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:07,547
I saw you over there earlier,

12
00:02:07,827 --> 00:02:10,787
taking down all those ash boxes.
Why did you do that?

13
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:15,067
There's a time limit for storing ashes.

14
00:02:15,387 --> 00:02:16,947
It can be months or years.

15
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:18,787
The maximum is twenty years.

16
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:22,906
Once time's up and not renewed,
they have to be removed.

17
00:02:23,586 --> 00:02:24,987
What happens after they're removed?

18
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:27,387
They go to the warehouse.

19
00:02:27,787 --> 00:02:31,626
Meanwhile, we try every way possible
to contact their families.

20
00:02:32,186 --> 00:02:33,667
If no one claims them in the end,

21
00:02:34,227 --> 00:02:36,306
they'll be buried together in batches.

22
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:39,746
So how long can they stay
in the warehouse?

23
00:02:40,306 --> 00:02:42,426
According to our rules, twelve months.

24
00:02:43,186 --> 00:02:45,186
So those
have all been there twelve months?

25
00:02:52,947 --> 00:02:54,586
What? Are you going to bury them now?

26
00:02:55,067 --> 00:02:56,387
In forty-five minutes.

27
00:02:57,267 --> 00:02:57,987
So precise?

28
00:02:58,706 --> 00:03:01,507
Because only precision ensures fairness.

29
00:03:02,306 --> 00:03:03,987
Alright, let's go. I won't hold you up.

30
00:03:20,866 --> 00:03:21,787
Just put it here?

31
00:03:22,787 --> 00:03:23,466
Thanks.

32
00:03:28,306 --> 00:03:29,387
He can never go home.

33
00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:34,387
But he's completely free now.

34
00:03:38,347 --> 00:03:40,227
You're not here
to keep me company, are you?

35
00:03:49,267 --> 00:03:50,466
What else do you need?

36
00:03:51,827 --> 00:03:53,227
Nothing. I'll head off now.

37
00:03:53,706 --> 00:03:55,426
Let's talk later. Bye.

38
00:04:09,026 --> 00:04:11,107
The provincial autopsy report is out.
Take a look.

39
00:04:12,306 --> 00:04:13,560
(Autopsy report)
It offers little more information

40
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,667
than we had in Qidaohezi.

41
00:04:15,026 --> 00:04:17,107
The key fatal injury is still not found.

42
00:04:22,426 --> 00:04:25,547
Given this, I need to go to Qingzhou
to see Professor Li.

43
00:04:25,907 --> 00:04:26,746
Now?

44
00:04:28,066 --> 00:04:28,746
I'll call him.

45
00:04:29,027 --> 00:04:29,626
You go ahead.

46
00:04:31,192 --> 00:04:32,728
Meng? What's up?

47
00:04:33,317 --> 00:04:36,547
Xiaoming, I've got a work trip
to Qingzhou in a couple of days.

48
00:04:37,186 --> 00:04:39,426
If you have time then, let's meet up.

49
00:04:39,826 --> 00:04:41,186
Sure, come find me.

50
00:04:42,306 --> 00:04:43,587
I saw Bai Shu recently.

51
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,547
Really?

52
00:04:46,227 --> 00:04:47,386
Message me when you come.

53
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:49,266
Got it. See you then.

54
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:50,987
Bye.

55
00:04:58,227 --> 00:04:59,227
(Qidaohezi, 2004)
Since I was little,

56
00:04:59,506 --> 00:05:01,266
I dreaded parent-teacher meetings
the most.

57
00:05:02,147 --> 00:05:05,426
Every time, my mom
would embarrass me somehow.

58
00:05:07,547 --> 00:05:11,907
My elementary school homeroom teacher
got into a fistfight with my mom.

59
00:05:12,347 --> 00:05:14,147
They fought all the way
to the sports field.

60
00:05:15,467 --> 00:05:16,907
Eventually, the whole school knew.

61
00:05:16,907 --> 00:05:18,547
Kept my head down
for an entire semester.

62
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,186
Why did they fight?

63
00:05:21,467 --> 00:05:23,826
That teacher said I was stupid
and should switch classes.

64
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:26,027
Education is for all. She deserved it.

65
00:05:26,266 --> 00:05:27,147
Your mom did it right.

66
00:05:29,426 --> 00:05:31,626
Why do you always take my mom's side?

67
00:05:32,066 --> 00:05:33,066
You get all upset

68
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:34,506
whenever I take your mom's side.

69
00:05:36,147 --> 00:05:36,826
It's different.

70
00:05:38,266 --> 00:05:39,626
How is it different?

71
00:05:40,306 --> 00:05:42,186
The grass is always greener
on the other side.

72
00:05:44,027 --> 00:05:46,626
Remember that night we went home?

73
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:48,626
My mom just hit me, and that was it.

74
00:05:49,227 --> 00:05:50,066
And your mom?

75
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:53,107
She spent time every day,
picking you up and dropping you off.

76
00:05:53,547 --> 00:05:55,027
Every time, she brought you clothes

77
00:05:55,107 --> 00:05:56,027
or food,

78
00:05:56,506 --> 00:05:57,784
afraid you'd be hungry or cold.

79
00:05:58,987 --> 00:06:00,626
My mom was just venting anger.

80
00:06:01,147 --> 00:06:03,107
Your mom genuinely cares about you.

81
00:06:03,626 --> 00:06:04,426
But what about you?

82
00:06:04,907 --> 00:06:06,227
Look at your attitude to her.

83
00:06:07,987 --> 00:06:11,186
I told you to say, 'I'm sorry, Mom.'

84
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:16,107
If I were your mom,
I would've slapped you long ago.

85
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:18,186
But your mom just smiles.

86
00:06:24,386 --> 00:06:26,506
See? You're getting upset again.

87
00:06:29,227 --> 00:06:31,227
You get to praise my mom,
but I can't praise yours?

88
00:06:32,707 --> 00:06:33,787
You're so petty.

89
00:06:42,787 --> 00:06:44,907
(Teacher's Office)
Ms. Zhou, I swear my mom is really sick.

90
00:06:45,107 --> 00:06:45,907
It's pretty serious.

91
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:48,746
Why is she sick
for every parent-teacher meeting?

92
00:06:50,506 --> 00:06:52,147
It's because of me. She's exhausted.

93
00:06:54,426 --> 00:06:55,467
Let your mom rest well.

94
00:06:55,587 --> 00:06:58,707
I'll do a home visit later
to tell her about the meeting.

95
00:06:59,227 --> 00:07:01,547
No, no need.
I'll listen and tell her myself.

96
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:02,266
It's fine.

97
00:07:02,386 --> 00:07:04,467
Don't worry.
I won't say anything bad about you.

98
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:10,547
I saw your mom
buying groceries this morning.

99
00:07:10,547 --> 00:07:12,227
No. What are you talking about?

100
00:07:13,787 --> 00:07:14,626
Your mom's sick?

101
00:07:15,506 --> 00:07:16,306
Who said so?

102
00:07:17,147 --> 00:07:19,306
I just heard you tell Ms. Zhou so.

103
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:20,626
Were you cursing her?

104
00:07:20,826 --> 00:07:22,186
Are you kidding me?

105
00:07:23,027 --> 00:07:25,186
Haven't I always been a sickness
on my mom's mind?

106
00:07:25,347 --> 00:07:26,107
It's not lying.

107
00:07:26,907 --> 00:07:27,987
Have you seen Bai Shu?

108
00:07:28,227 --> 00:07:29,306
Likely went to see her mom.

109
00:07:30,186 --> 00:07:31,186
Won't you see your mom?

110
00:07:32,147 --> 00:07:32,946
She doesn't need me.

111
00:07:40,107 --> 00:07:41,347
Why are you here so early?

112
00:07:42,147 --> 00:07:43,987
I want to talk
with your homeroom teacher.

113
00:07:44,746 --> 00:07:45,626
About what?

114
00:07:47,626 --> 00:07:49,027
Don't you want to get into Yucai?

115
00:07:49,787 --> 00:07:51,107
I fully support it.

116
00:07:52,107 --> 00:07:54,467
But I think with your grades,

117
00:07:55,306 --> 00:07:58,467
studying alongside other students
at school right now

118
00:07:58,946 --> 00:08:01,027
is just wasting your energy and time.

119
00:08:03,987 --> 00:08:05,227
I'd like a long leave for you.

120
00:08:05,626 --> 00:08:09,147
On one hand, you can study at home
at your own pace.

121
00:08:09,787 --> 00:08:13,066
On the other hand,
I can cook you some good food.

122
00:08:13,506 --> 00:08:15,547
You're too skinny. You need nutrition.

123
00:08:17,147 --> 00:08:17,787
No need.

124
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:21,107
Seniors can't take leave
unless it's special.

125
00:08:21,547 --> 00:08:22,746
The teacher won't approve it.

126
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:24,426
You are the special case.

127
00:08:25,107 --> 00:08:26,626
Why wouldn't they approve your leave?

128
00:08:27,707 --> 00:08:28,306
Besides,

129
00:08:29,147 --> 00:08:30,547
even if you skip the entrance exam,

130
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,026
I can still get you into Yucai.

131
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:41,146
What's that attitude?

132
00:08:42,746 --> 00:08:44,227
I'm supporting you so much.

133
00:08:44,987 --> 00:08:46,026
And that's your attitude?

134
00:08:50,146 --> 00:08:52,107
I want to invite Ren Xiaoming
to our home.

135
00:08:55,187 --> 00:08:56,266
W-What do you want?

136
00:08:58,347 --> 00:09:00,187
Didn't you eat at her place?

137
00:09:00,386 --> 00:09:01,827
Weren't you happy eating there?

138
00:09:02,506 --> 00:09:04,347
Didn't you write that in your diary?

139
00:09:04,746 --> 00:09:06,906
"That's my family.

140
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:11,146
That place feels more like home."

141
00:09:15,187 --> 00:09:16,146
You read my diary?

142
00:09:19,227 --> 00:09:21,827
I read every entry
of your diary carefully.

143
00:09:26,506 --> 00:09:28,546
You really worry me to death.

144
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:33,626
I'll go talk to Ren Xiaoming later.

145
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:35,266
No need.

146
00:09:36,746 --> 00:09:37,947
Aren't you two good friends?

147
00:09:38,987 --> 00:09:40,467
Why not invite her over?

148
00:09:42,307 --> 00:09:43,626
She's not my good friend.

149
00:09:45,427 --> 00:09:46,347
Really?

150
00:09:47,506 --> 00:09:48,792
Just a playmate when I'm bored.

151
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:51,947
Bored? How can you be bored?

152
00:09:56,987 --> 00:09:58,187
Since she's just a playmate,

153
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,947
there's no need for her to come over.

154
00:10:04,227 --> 00:10:04,827
Playmate?

155
00:10:21,528 --> 00:10:24,304
♪On the banyan tree by the pond♪

156
00:10:25,427 --> 00:10:26,266
Acting crazy again?

157
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:27,626
Get lost.

158
00:10:28,347 --> 00:10:29,307
Who pissed you off?

159
00:10:31,347 --> 00:10:32,467
None of your business.

160
00:10:32,746 --> 00:10:34,506
Are we friends? We're playmates.

161
00:10:35,947 --> 00:10:36,467
Huh?

162
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:39,107
Playmate, do you get it?

163
00:10:40,331 --> 00:10:43,227
♪Still chirping away nonstop♪

164
00:10:43,227 --> 00:10:44,026
What's a playmate?

165
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:45,866
A buddy to play with? Isn't that nice?

166
00:10:47,107 --> 00:10:48,347
Am I your playmate?

167
00:10:48,746 --> 00:10:49,666
Stay away from me.

168
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,326
♪The welfare shop has everything♪

169
00:10:59,736 --> 00:11:02,947
♪But not a dime in my pocket♪

170
00:11:02,947 --> 00:11:04,347
The meeting began a while ago.

171
00:11:04,947 --> 00:11:05,976
Why aren't you in class?

172
00:11:07,866 --> 00:11:09,546
What does the meeting
have to do with me?

173
00:11:09,947 --> 00:11:11,107
My parents aren't even there.

174
00:11:12,347 --> 00:11:12,947
Boring.

175
00:11:14,827 --> 00:11:16,587
What's with the eye-rolling
and acting crazy?

176
00:11:16,587 --> 00:11:17,866
Dude, you're seriously sick.

177
00:11:18,187 --> 00:11:20,107
Pfft, who's your dude?

178
00:11:20,107 --> 00:11:20,746
Playmate.

179
00:11:20,746 --> 00:11:22,940
♪Snacks in my mouth♪

180
00:11:23,707 --> 00:11:24,427
What playmate?

181
00:11:24,952 --> 00:11:28,277
♪The first love of my childhood
in my heart♪

182
00:11:29,672 --> 00:11:32,267
♪Always waiting until bedtime♪

183
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,626
♪To find out
only a little homework's done♪

184
00:11:34,626 --> 00:11:35,707
Have you seen Xiaoming?

185
00:11:37,227 --> 00:11:38,347
What? Did you two fight?

186
00:11:39,015 --> 00:11:41,546
Huh? What's wrong?

187
00:11:42,146 --> 00:11:44,587
She called me 'playmate'
and razzed me. What's going on?

188
00:11:46,266 --> 00:11:47,026
Playmate?

189
00:11:50,427 --> 00:11:51,427
She heard it.

190
00:11:51,947 --> 00:11:52,467
What?

191
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:54,386
Where did she go?

192
00:11:56,227 --> 00:11:57,026
Back to the class.

193
00:11:57,912 --> 00:12:01,163
♪A hazy, bewildered childhood♪

194
00:12:01,906 --> 00:12:02,906
What the heck?

195
00:12:04,266 --> 00:12:05,026
Parents,

196
00:12:05,587 --> 00:12:07,666
among the five subjects
your kids are studying,

197
00:12:07,987 --> 00:12:10,506
namely, Chinese, math,

198
00:12:10,827 --> 00:12:13,146
English, chemistry, and physics,

199
00:12:13,506 --> 00:12:14,520
each is worth 100 points.

200
00:12:14,827 --> 00:12:16,746
That adds up to 500 points total.

201
00:12:17,427 --> 00:12:18,906
The score cutoffs are:

202
00:12:19,187 --> 00:12:21,427
270 points for vocational schools
and technical colleges,

203
00:12:21,707 --> 00:12:24,026
320 points for regular high schools,

204
00:12:24,307 --> 00:12:27,427
and over 370 points
for key high schools.

205
00:12:27,906 --> 00:12:30,307
These are based on last year's
score cutoff standards.

206
00:12:30,827 --> 00:12:32,152
In our city, Yucai is

207
00:12:32,457 --> 00:12:33,516
- the key high school
- (Fanning herself.)

208
00:12:33,516 --> 00:12:35,026
- with the highest cutoff score.
- (Shaking her legs.)

209
00:12:35,506 --> 00:12:36,728
Its cutoff score has reached

210
00:12:36,728 --> 00:12:38,026
- 450 points.
- (Nodding.)

211
00:12:38,386 --> 00:12:39,347
- Which means
- (Mouth open.)

212
00:12:39,546 --> 00:12:40,827
among these five subjects,

213
00:12:40,987 --> 00:12:42,026
- at most ten points
- Close your mouth.

214
00:12:42,187 --> 00:12:43,587
per subject can be lost.

215
00:12:45,107 --> 00:12:45,666
Move aside.

216
00:12:48,032 --> 00:12:50,796
♪Nobody could tell me♪

217
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:54,855
♪If immortals lived in the mountains♪

218
00:12:55,648 --> 00:12:57,752
♪How many days spent♪

219
00:12:57,752 --> 00:13:02,677
♪Staring blankly at the sky alone♪

220
00:13:03,935 --> 00:13:05,906
♪So curious♪

221
00:13:05,906 --> 00:13:06,746
Xiaoming.

222
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:11,268
♪So lonely childhood♪

223
00:13:14,909 --> 00:13:17,577
♪Dragonflies flew over in the sunlight♪

224
00:13:17,653 --> 00:13:22,014
♪Over vast stretches
of green rice fields♪

225
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:25,770
♪Watercolors, crayons, and kaleidoscope♪

226
00:13:25,868 --> 00:13:29,773
♪Couldn't draw that rainbow
on the horizon♪

227
00:13:32,427 --> 00:13:33,546
What took you so long?

228
00:13:34,746 --> 00:13:35,707
None of your business.

229
00:13:36,546 --> 00:13:37,307
Where did you go?

230
00:13:38,707 --> 00:13:39,546
Go cook for me.

231
00:13:39,906 --> 00:13:41,307
I'm so hungry. All I had was sugar.

232
00:13:41,592 --> 00:13:42,930
♪Longing to tomorrow♪

233
00:13:43,039 --> 00:13:46,290
♪Longing to grow up in childhood♪

234
00:13:46,290 --> 00:13:49,107
♪Oh, day after day♪

235
00:13:49,107 --> 00:13:50,906
Let me show you some moves
to wake you up.

236
00:13:56,827 --> 00:14:01,107
Sunflower Acupointer!

237
00:14:01,107 --> 00:14:02,587
Get off me!

238
00:14:05,506 --> 00:14:06,786
Here comes a big one.

239
00:14:12,187 --> 00:14:12,866
Mountain Crusher!

240
00:14:13,107 --> 00:14:13,987
What are you doing?

241
00:14:14,546 --> 00:14:16,187
You and your Mountain Crusher?

242
00:14:16,307 --> 00:14:18,187
I'll give you a taste
of your own medicine.

243
00:14:18,626 --> 00:14:19,546
Bull Demon King!

244
00:14:19,746 --> 00:14:20,506
Stop that.

245
00:14:24,506 --> 00:14:25,107
Pah!

246
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:26,827
Pah!

247
00:14:26,827 --> 00:14:27,587
Pah!

248
00:14:27,587 --> 00:14:28,347
Pah!

249
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:29,307
Pah!

250
00:14:29,786 --> 00:14:30,427
Pah!

251
00:14:30,427 --> 00:14:31,026
Pah!

252
00:14:42,146 --> 00:14:42,906
Come in.

253
00:14:52,546 --> 00:14:53,227
Ren Xiaoming.

254
00:14:54,347 --> 00:14:55,146
He started it.

255
00:14:55,307 --> 00:14:56,026
She started it.

256
00:14:56,427 --> 00:14:57,266
You started it.

257
00:14:57,307 --> 00:14:58,146
You started it.

258
00:14:58,386 --> 00:14:59,107
- You started it.
- Meiyan.

259
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:00,107
- You started it.
- I'm leaving.

260
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:00,666
- Maybe another day.
- She started it.

261
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:01,666
- Wait.
- Another day.

262
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:02,546
He started it.

263
00:15:03,506 --> 00:15:05,266
Sun? Sun?

264
00:15:05,626 --> 00:15:06,626
Who's 'Sun'?

265
00:15:08,026 --> 00:15:08,786
The monkey.

266
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,187
Go ahead, hit me.

267
00:15:27,587 --> 00:15:29,506
You're hitting me
because that man left, right?

268
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:39,506
Why the sugar jar?

269
00:15:39,947 --> 00:15:40,746
To eat sugar.

270
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:42,266
Haven't eaten?

271
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:44,187
I did.

272
00:15:46,506 --> 00:15:47,187
Go to bed.

273
00:15:50,026 --> 00:15:50,906
Traitor.

274
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:11,347
Sit down.

275
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:17,187
Come here and sit down.

276
00:16:24,947 --> 00:16:26,307
You're practically an adult now.

277
00:16:26,947 --> 00:16:28,386
I need to clarify a few things.

278
00:16:29,187 --> 00:16:30,146
Ren Xiaoming, remember.

279
00:16:30,947 --> 00:16:33,626
I will never hit you because of any man.

280
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:37,467
Except for Xiaofei.

281
00:16:41,307 --> 00:16:42,626
The three of us are family.

282
00:16:44,026 --> 00:16:45,347
Everyone else is an outsider.

283
00:16:47,146 --> 00:16:48,707
Outsiders might help us sometimes,

284
00:16:48,707 --> 00:16:51,427
but ultimately, they can't be relied on.

285
00:16:54,546 --> 00:16:55,626
I only have you two.

286
00:16:57,467 --> 00:16:58,666
You two only have me.

287
00:16:59,987 --> 00:17:00,987
When I'm gone,

288
00:17:02,587 --> 00:17:05,387
you and Xiaofei
will only have each other.

289
00:17:10,947 --> 00:17:12,627
I know you hate this family.

290
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:15,467
I also know you look down on me.

291
00:17:16,826 --> 00:17:18,947
One day you'll leave and go far away.

292
00:17:20,266 --> 00:17:21,227
But promise me.

293
00:17:22,306 --> 00:17:23,427
If I die...

294
00:17:27,907 --> 00:17:30,586
if I die, you can't abandon Xiaofei.

295
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:32,346
You are his sister.

296
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,506
I don't look down on you.

297
00:17:41,506 --> 00:17:42,147
I just

298
00:17:44,187 --> 00:17:45,147
don't want to be you.

299
00:17:52,147 --> 00:17:54,427
I just want to see the world outside.

300
00:17:59,026 --> 00:18:00,786
A few tears,
and you tore off so much paper?

301
00:18:12,187 --> 00:18:12,746
Xiaofei?

302
00:18:19,026 --> 00:18:20,467
Why are you still eating sugar?

303
00:18:21,187 --> 00:18:22,040
I'm hungry.

304
00:18:22,427 --> 00:18:23,387
You haven't eaten?

305
00:18:24,106 --> 00:18:25,506
I haven't had time to cook yet.

306
00:18:28,026 --> 00:18:29,586
Just wait. I will cook for you two.

307
00:18:29,987 --> 00:18:30,707
I'll be quick.

308
00:18:31,746 --> 00:18:32,907
I will make noodles for you.

309
00:18:33,427 --> 00:18:34,506
Just wait. I'll be quick.

310
00:18:46,106 --> 00:18:49,106
See? This watch is super waterproof.
I just got it.

311
00:18:49,106 --> 00:18:50,187
Shaking your wrist all day.

312
00:18:50,187 --> 00:18:51,387
Don't break it.

313
00:18:53,826 --> 00:18:55,546
This watch even has a calendar.

314
00:18:55,826 --> 00:18:57,947
I can tell who's going through menopause
at a glance.

315
00:19:01,746 --> 00:19:03,026
See? This is menopause.

316
00:19:03,586 --> 00:19:04,187
Amazing.

317
00:19:04,266 --> 00:19:05,627
Xiaoming, menopause?

318
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:06,826
Get lost.

319
00:19:06,947 --> 00:19:08,427
See? Classic menopause line.

320
00:19:08,427 --> 00:19:10,106
- Get lost.
- Teacher's here.

321
00:19:10,306 --> 00:19:11,026
Teacher's here.

322
00:19:11,026 --> 00:19:11,907
Teacher's here. Hurry.

323
00:19:21,947 --> 00:19:22,907
All rise.

324
00:19:25,106 --> 00:19:25,746
Good day, class.

325
00:19:26,147 --> 00:19:29,026
- Good day, sir.
- Good day, sir.

326
00:19:29,266 --> 00:19:30,104
Please sit down.

327
00:19:31,306 --> 00:19:35,147
Academic affairs office needs to gather
data on graduating seniors' future plans.

328
00:19:36,106 --> 00:19:37,746
Those who aim for high schools,
hands up.

329
00:19:40,947 --> 00:19:42,106
Okay, put your hands down.

330
00:19:42,786 --> 00:19:44,987
Anyone aiming for municipal key schools?
Hands up.

331
00:19:46,266 --> 00:19:48,106
Anyone? Municipal key schools?

332
00:19:48,826 --> 00:19:49,427
Sir.

333
00:19:50,826 --> 00:19:51,667
What? You want it?

334
00:19:51,826 --> 00:19:53,187
The one fit isn't here today.

335
00:19:54,147 --> 00:19:54,826
Who's not here?

336
00:19:55,627 --> 00:19:56,187
Bai Shu.

337
00:20:02,106 --> 00:20:03,266
Anyone else then?

338
00:20:05,387 --> 00:20:05,987
Anyone else?

339
00:20:13,586 --> 00:20:14,346
Continue the class.

340
00:20:14,586 --> 00:20:15,147
Yes, sir.

341
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:16,147
Sir.

342
00:20:18,907 --> 00:20:19,826
I want to apply for it.

343
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:21,400
I want to go to Yucai.

344
00:20:23,187 --> 00:20:24,106
You want to apply?

345
00:20:24,746 --> 00:20:25,667
What's your name?

346
00:20:26,907 --> 00:20:27,667
Ren Xiaoming.

347
00:20:28,106 --> 00:20:28,627
Good.

348
00:20:31,147 --> 00:20:31,826
Good.

349
00:20:32,187 --> 00:20:32,746
Good.

350
00:20:38,627 --> 00:20:39,826
(I want to be like Bai Shu.)

351
00:20:40,707 --> 00:20:42,026
(We'll both go to a key school.)

352
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:45,346
Bai Shu,

353
00:20:46,627 --> 00:20:48,586
come here and call your dad.

354
00:20:49,227 --> 00:20:50,826
You did so well on this mock exam.

355
00:20:51,506 --> 00:20:53,227
He'll be thrilled when he finds out.

356
00:20:54,266 --> 00:20:54,907
Come on.

357
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:00,707
Hurry. It's ringing.

358
00:21:06,904 --> 00:21:07,670
Hello?

359
00:21:08,387 --> 00:21:09,187
This is Bai Shu.

360
00:21:11,707 --> 00:21:12,546
Bai Shu is dead.

361
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:16,467
Say something.

362
00:21:17,746 --> 00:21:18,387
He hung up.

363
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:24,147
Without saying anything?

364
00:21:24,826 --> 00:21:25,467
He said...

365
00:21:28,306 --> 00:21:28,907
What'd he say?

366
00:21:30,746 --> 00:21:31,947
He said Bai Shu is dead.

367
00:21:37,106 --> 00:21:38,520
However you urge me to please him,

368
00:21:38,987 --> 00:21:41,106
he knows very well that I'm not Bai Shu.

369
00:21:42,187 --> 00:21:43,467
The real Bai Shu is dead.

370
00:21:47,786 --> 00:21:49,266
She's not dead!

371
00:21:50,306 --> 00:21:52,187
Aren't you Bai Shu?

372
00:21:53,427 --> 00:21:55,147
Aren't you alive and well?

373
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,667
My daughter isn't dead.

374
00:21:57,746 --> 00:21:59,907
Don't say she's dead.

375
00:22:00,427 --> 00:22:02,867
My daughter is not dead.

376
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:21,106
I only have you now.

377
00:22:23,306 --> 00:22:24,147
Don't cry.

378
00:22:27,506 --> 00:22:28,546
I won't cry.

379
00:22:29,746 --> 00:22:30,867
I won't cry.

380
00:22:32,346 --> 00:22:33,467
I won't cry.

381
00:22:35,106 --> 00:22:35,907
Come on.

382
00:22:36,427 --> 00:22:37,106
Come on.

383
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:38,746
Be careful.

384
00:22:43,106 --> 00:22:44,266
Put on your slippers.

385
00:22:49,187 --> 00:22:51,147
I won't call that man ever again.

386
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:53,786
He wants a divorce? No way.

387
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:28,907
You get some rest.

388
00:24:42,506 --> 00:24:44,467
Bai Shu? Bai Shu?

389
00:24:44,826 --> 00:24:46,306
It's me, Ren Xiaoming, Bai Shu.

390
00:24:47,026 --> 00:24:48,506
Bai Shu, it's Ren Xiaoming.

391
00:24:48,907 --> 00:24:50,106
Bai Shu, are you in there?

392
00:24:50,627 --> 00:24:51,306
Bai Shu?

393
00:24:52,147 --> 00:24:54,227
It's me. It's me. Bai Shu, you there?

394
00:24:54,227 --> 00:24:56,106
Stop yelling. Quiet down.

395
00:24:56,546 --> 00:24:58,306
What are you doing? Who are you?

396
00:24:59,147 --> 00:25:00,387
I saw you on security camera.

397
00:25:00,427 --> 00:25:01,947
You've been circling around.

398
00:25:02,026 --> 00:25:03,106
Are you security too?

399
00:25:03,427 --> 00:25:04,506
I came to see my classmate.

400
00:25:04,826 --> 00:25:05,467
And who is that?

401
00:25:05,506 --> 00:25:06,907
Wait. Look.

402
00:25:07,227 --> 00:25:07,826
Bai Shu.

403
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:10,947
Go to your friend.

404
00:25:11,667 --> 00:25:12,427
She needs you.

405
00:25:16,106 --> 00:25:17,026
Stop looking.

406
00:25:18,506 --> 00:25:19,306
Did you see?

407
00:25:20,266 --> 00:25:21,427
The curtains are closed.

408
00:25:21,546 --> 00:25:23,064
Does she want anything to do with you?

409
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:25,147
Does she even know who you are?

410
00:25:25,266 --> 00:25:26,266
Just go.

411
00:25:26,707 --> 00:25:27,387
If you need one,

412
00:25:27,467 --> 00:25:28,667
I can be your classmate, okay?

413
00:25:28,947 --> 00:25:30,826
- Go.
- Wait. She really is my classmate.

414
00:25:31,867 --> 00:25:32,667
What classmate?

415
00:25:32,867 --> 00:25:34,667
Hurry up. Just go. Move.

416
00:25:36,187 --> 00:25:38,387
Be a good kid and listen. Let's go.

417
00:25:43,227 --> 00:25:45,707
Stop looking.
Does she want to deal with you?

418
00:26:05,593 --> 00:26:08,491
(Qidian Middle School,
Qidaohezi District, La City)

419
00:27:21,786 --> 00:27:24,387
Ren Xiaoming. It's you, right?

420
00:27:27,506 --> 00:27:28,306
It's not me.

421
00:27:36,387 --> 00:27:37,106
What's wrong?

422
00:27:39,187 --> 00:27:41,387
Bai Shu was just here crying too.

423
00:27:42,346 --> 00:27:44,227
Are you upset about the same thing?

424
00:27:46,506 --> 00:27:48,106
She told you?

425
00:27:49,987 --> 00:27:52,187
Why do you think
she closed the curtains?

426
00:27:55,707 --> 00:27:57,467
She probably thought I was embarrassing.

427
00:28:00,907 --> 00:28:03,106
Are you and Bai Shu best friends?

428
00:28:05,947 --> 00:28:07,467
I consider her my best friend.

429
00:28:08,907 --> 00:28:10,387
She doesn't consider me a friend.

430
00:28:11,266 --> 00:28:12,266
She said it herself?

431
00:28:16,667 --> 00:28:18,266
But have you asked her?

432
00:28:21,826 --> 00:28:23,746
Why did she pretend she doesn't know me?

433
00:28:26,387 --> 00:28:27,387
Here's my advice.

434
00:28:28,227 --> 00:28:30,586
Since you think she's your best friend,

435
00:28:30,947 --> 00:28:33,867
you should give her a chance
to explain it to you herself.

436
00:28:34,707 --> 00:28:37,546
Decide whether to stay friends
after she tells you.

437
00:28:44,786 --> 00:28:45,786
Go find her.

438
00:28:52,707 --> 00:28:53,427
Bai Shu.

439
00:28:56,346 --> 00:28:57,106
Bai Shu.

440
00:29:04,586 --> 00:29:06,306
Wait, Bai Shu. Wait...

441
00:29:39,106 --> 00:29:39,627
Be good.

442
00:30:27,026 --> 00:30:29,467
Come on, don't miss out!

443
00:30:29,586 --> 00:30:30,746
Feel free to look and touch!

444
00:30:30,746 --> 00:30:32,707
Our fabrics are top quality!

445
00:30:32,867 --> 00:30:35,387
Do you think I was out of my mind?

446
00:30:35,387 --> 00:30:37,106
Why did I have to run over right then?

447
00:30:37,227 --> 00:30:40,306
I've answered this question
at least twenty times today.

448
00:30:40,907 --> 00:30:42,826
Bai Shu won't talk to me anymore.

449
00:30:43,867 --> 00:30:45,867
So what if she talks to you or not?

450
00:30:45,987 --> 00:30:47,586
What? You can't live without her?

451
00:30:48,187 --> 00:30:50,627
Bai Shu isn't like that.

452
00:30:51,106 --> 00:30:52,826
She definitely has a secret
she can't tell.

453
00:30:53,467 --> 00:30:54,627
A secret she can't tell?

454
00:30:54,867 --> 00:30:55,987
Your imagination is wild.

455
00:30:57,306 --> 00:30:58,306
I mean it.

456
00:30:58,627 --> 00:31:01,627
And I think her mom is really strange.

457
00:31:02,387 --> 00:31:05,106
She's super gentle and polite
when I'm around.

458
00:31:05,187 --> 00:31:06,387
But you don't know.

459
00:31:06,467 --> 00:31:08,227
She hit Bai Shu way too hard.

460
00:31:08,467 --> 00:31:10,026
Just slapped her right across the face.

461
00:31:11,227 --> 00:31:12,867
What's the big deal?

462
00:31:12,867 --> 00:31:14,987
My mom hits me too.

463
00:31:14,987 --> 00:31:16,786
She's broken
several broom handles on me.

464
00:31:17,306 --> 00:31:18,387
That's different.

465
00:31:19,187 --> 00:31:20,586
My mom hits me a lot too.

466
00:31:21,506 --> 00:31:23,346
But she never hits my face that hard.

467
00:31:23,826 --> 00:31:25,387
Even if she does aim for my face,

468
00:31:25,907 --> 00:31:27,947
she deliberately misses a bit.

469
00:31:28,746 --> 00:31:30,187
Half on the face, half on the neck.

470
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:33,987
And it's more of a push than a slap.

471
00:31:34,627 --> 00:31:36,306
What's the difference?

472
00:31:37,346 --> 00:31:38,187
Don't you get it?

473
00:31:38,786 --> 00:31:39,667
Get what?

474
00:31:41,667 --> 00:31:44,346
Slapping a girl's face
is the most humiliating way to hit her.

475
00:31:45,826 --> 00:31:46,627
I didn't know that.

476
00:31:46,746 --> 00:31:48,786
If you don't go home soon,
your mom will hit you.

477
00:31:49,346 --> 00:31:50,467
She's on night duty today.

478
00:31:55,667 --> 00:31:58,266
Why did I have to run over right then?

479
00:31:58,907 --> 00:32:01,306
Seriously, go.

480
00:32:01,387 --> 00:32:02,907
You're scaring off my customers.

481
00:32:03,346 --> 00:32:04,546
I must be out of my mind.

482
00:32:04,826 --> 00:32:05,826
I just had to run over

483
00:32:05,826 --> 00:32:06,987
and see her getting slapped.

484
00:32:07,266 --> 00:32:09,187
Well, you sound like a broken record.

485
00:32:09,266 --> 00:32:11,227
Just go. Please.

486
00:32:13,026 --> 00:32:14,147
Was I out of my mind?

487
00:32:14,506 --> 00:32:15,746
Just go home.

488
00:32:32,026 --> 00:32:33,227
What are you doing?

489
00:32:34,147 --> 00:32:35,306
Are you trying for Yucai?

490
00:32:35,427 --> 00:32:36,346
You need to study hard.

491
00:32:38,227 --> 00:32:38,987
Not your business.

492
00:32:40,586 --> 00:32:41,786
I'll get you some water.

493
00:32:47,467 --> 00:32:49,506
(That slap must've really hurt Bai Shu.)

494
00:32:50,506 --> 00:32:51,867
(She's so proud.)

495
00:32:53,387 --> 00:32:55,187
(She won't stop coming to school,
will she?)

496
00:32:57,147 --> 00:32:58,586
(What should I do then?)

497
00:33:02,066 --> 00:33:03,586
Here, have some water.

498
00:33:05,306 --> 00:33:06,346
Put it aside.

499
00:33:06,947 --> 00:33:08,746
Look at you, no appreciation.

500
00:33:10,147 --> 00:33:11,306
She's gone. Now you show up.

501
00:33:16,387 --> 00:33:17,707
If you get tired of math,

502
00:33:17,746 --> 00:33:18,786
switch to Chinese.

503
00:33:19,786 --> 00:33:21,432
Recite the Northern Expedition Memorial.

504
00:33:22,347 --> 00:33:24,191
(Northern Expedition Memorial)

505
00:33:25,947 --> 00:33:27,786
Which boy wrote you this note?

506
00:33:29,026 --> 00:33:31,707
Xiaoming, I saw you that day.

507
00:33:32,026 --> 00:33:33,826
- But I didn't help you.
- (But I didn't help you.)

508
00:33:34,467 --> 00:33:35,026
(I was wrong.)

509
00:33:35,707 --> 00:33:36,746
(But please believe me,)

510
00:33:37,187 --> 00:33:39,786
(I wasn't ashamed to admit
you're my friend.)

511
00:33:40,467 --> 00:33:41,667
(You're not just my friend.)

512
00:33:42,106 --> 00:33:43,907
(You're my best friend ever.)

513
00:33:44,867 --> 00:33:45,667
(My only friend.)

514
00:33:48,627 --> 00:33:49,387
Where you going?

515
00:33:51,467 --> 00:33:52,387
You can't leave.

516
00:33:52,546 --> 00:33:53,467
- Stop.
- You can't leave.

517
00:33:53,467 --> 00:33:54,506
- Let go.
- You can't leave.

518
00:33:54,506 --> 00:33:55,106
Leave me alone.

519
00:33:55,746 --> 00:33:56,907
Stay home.

520
00:34:14,706 --> 00:34:16,026
Why is it him again?

521
00:34:21,907 --> 00:34:22,706
Let me help.

522
00:34:23,787 --> 00:34:24,787
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

523
00:34:29,947 --> 00:34:30,787
Why is it you again?

524
00:34:31,226 --> 00:34:31,827
Don't run.

525
00:34:32,947 --> 00:34:33,706
Stop right there!

526
00:34:52,626 --> 00:34:55,347
Bai Shu, I found the note in the book.

527
00:34:55,347 --> 00:34:56,226
Come down.

528
00:34:57,026 --> 00:34:58,867
I'm not mad anymore. Come down.

529
00:34:59,146 --> 00:35:00,186
Then just open the window.

530
00:35:00,186 --> 00:35:01,626
Bai Shu, come down.

531
00:35:01,626 --> 00:35:03,626
I'm not mad anymore. Come down.

532
00:35:04,427 --> 00:35:05,307
Come down.

533
00:35:05,787 --> 00:35:06,947
- I'm not mad anymore.
- Quiet.

534
00:35:06,947 --> 00:35:08,267
- Come down. Let's talk.
- Quiet.

535
00:35:08,267 --> 00:35:09,626
- Be quiet.
- Bai Shu, get down.

536
00:35:09,626 --> 00:35:10,907
- Stop yelling.
- Don't pull me.

537
00:35:11,307 --> 00:35:12,587
- Bai Shu, come down.
- Let's go.

538
00:35:12,587 --> 00:35:14,347
I'm really not angry anymore. Come down.

539
00:35:14,387 --> 00:35:15,146
I'll call the cops.

540
00:35:15,146 --> 00:35:17,026
I have something to tell you, Bai Shu.

541
00:35:17,026 --> 00:35:18,787
- Stop yelling, or I'll be fired.
- Bai Shu.

542
00:35:20,427 --> 00:35:21,787
Listen up, Kitten Face.

543
00:35:22,186 --> 00:35:24,787
Don't let me catch you
in this neighborhood again, got it?

544
00:35:25,026 --> 00:35:25,867
If I see you again...

545
00:35:26,907 --> 00:35:27,827
Who'd want to come?

546
00:35:27,827 --> 00:35:29,066
Dog poop everywhere.

547
00:35:29,186 --> 00:35:29,907
You...

548
00:35:32,626 --> 00:35:33,907
No dog poop for you.

549
00:37:00,787 --> 00:37:01,787
Why drink water?

550
00:37:01,787 --> 00:37:02,907
You want ice cream soup?

551
00:37:05,867 --> 00:37:06,706
What ice cream soup?

552
00:37:08,066 --> 00:37:09,427
I bought you ten ice creams.

553
00:37:09,787 --> 00:37:11,427
Who knew you don't have a fridge?

554
00:37:11,626 --> 00:37:12,467
They all melted.

555
00:37:12,787 --> 00:37:13,787
So just drink the soup.

556
00:37:14,827 --> 00:37:15,947
You have a fridge, so what?

557
00:37:16,347 --> 00:37:17,752
Your doorstep is full of dog poop.

558
00:37:18,787 --> 00:37:20,546
Kitten stepped right in dog poop?

559
00:37:20,787 --> 00:37:21,706
You're something else.

560
00:37:23,387 --> 00:37:24,347
Who's Kitten?

561
00:37:24,787 --> 00:37:26,226
Take a look yourself. Who's Kitten?

562
00:37:31,787 --> 00:37:33,506
Ren Xiaofei, was it you?

563
00:38:00,907 --> 00:38:02,787
I closed the curtains not to ignore you.

564
00:38:04,186 --> 00:38:05,706
But to pretend you couldn't see me.

565
00:38:07,307 --> 00:38:08,066
Why?

566
00:38:09,186 --> 00:38:10,506
Can I tell you later?

567
00:38:12,427 --> 00:38:13,347
Just don't lie to me.

568
00:38:13,347 --> 00:38:14,506
You don't even have to talk.

569
00:38:20,307 --> 00:38:21,666
Why did your mom hit you?

570
00:38:26,347 --> 00:38:28,706
My mom hits me too.
No need to be embarrassed.

571
00:38:32,666 --> 00:38:34,066
Because she was happy that day.

572
00:38:35,467 --> 00:38:36,387
But I was really down.

573
00:38:38,186 --> 00:38:39,267
Being down gets you hit?

574
00:38:40,186 --> 00:38:41,467
Our moods were out of sync.

575
00:38:43,032 --> 00:38:44,226
She said I was opposing her.

576
00:38:44,827 --> 00:38:45,666
I said no.

577
00:38:46,827 --> 00:38:47,867
She said I was lying.

578
00:38:49,026 --> 00:38:50,907
I said, "Fine, then I am opposing you."

579
00:38:51,827 --> 00:38:52,586
Then she hit me,

580
00:38:54,506 --> 00:38:55,586
saying I was provoking her.

581
00:38:56,827 --> 00:38:57,827
Your mom...

582
00:38:57,827 --> 00:38:59,256
Call her 'that person' from now on.

583
00:39:02,787 --> 00:39:05,146
Does that person hit you often?

584
00:39:05,347 --> 00:39:06,907
She never hit me before.

585
00:39:08,666 --> 00:39:09,666
It was the first time.

586
00:39:10,347 --> 00:39:12,427
That person seems quite kind.

587
00:39:12,787 --> 00:39:14,066
Why would she hit so hard?

588
00:39:18,947 --> 00:39:19,987
She's good at pretending.

589
00:39:20,626 --> 00:39:22,947
One way in front of others,
another way at home.

590
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:25,186
She hates me having friends.

591
00:39:26,186 --> 00:39:28,427
Even if it's one friend,
she drives them away.

592
00:39:29,947 --> 00:39:31,106
She never does it openly.

593
00:39:32,307 --> 00:39:34,387
The end result is
I can't have any friends.

594
00:39:36,387 --> 00:39:37,427
Why does she do that?

595
00:39:39,787 --> 00:39:40,427
Control.

596
00:39:44,987 --> 00:39:46,347
She has to control everything.

597
00:39:48,467 --> 00:39:50,427
Everything in that house, including me.

598
00:39:51,427 --> 00:39:53,146
My whole self and all my thoughts.

599
00:39:53,186 --> 00:39:54,787
She has to know and control them.

600
00:39:55,827 --> 00:39:56,907
That's creepy.

601
00:39:57,546 --> 00:39:58,626
It wasn't me who said that.

602
00:39:59,706 --> 00:40:00,626
Her husband said it.

603
00:40:02,267 --> 00:40:04,347
I heard it once when they were fighting.

604
00:40:05,506 --> 00:40:07,626
So did they divorce?

605
00:40:08,787 --> 00:40:11,146
No, that person didn't agree to divorce.

606
00:40:12,307 --> 00:40:13,026
So he left.

607
00:40:13,987 --> 00:40:16,307
He probably works out of town now
and rarely comes back.

608
00:40:18,226 --> 00:40:19,626
So she can't control others.

609
00:40:21,307 --> 00:40:22,267
She controls only me.

610
00:40:24,307 --> 00:40:25,827
Well, she can't control me.

611
00:40:27,347 --> 00:40:28,467
I'll always be your friend.

612
00:40:29,666 --> 00:40:30,787
No one can drive me away.

613
00:40:36,026 --> 00:40:38,827
Xiaoming, no matter
what she does to you,

614
00:40:40,467 --> 00:40:42,787
don't be scared and tell me.

615
00:40:43,506 --> 00:40:44,947
I'll tell her with my life

616
00:40:46,947 --> 00:40:48,267
that we'll always be friends.

617
00:40:54,146 --> 00:40:56,146
Okay, deal.

618
00:40:59,467 --> 00:41:00,267
Deal.

619
00:41:01,347 --> 00:41:04,947
Pinky swear, a hundred years,
no take-backs.

620
00:41:04,987 --> 00:41:06,066
Whoever breaks it is a dog.

621
00:41:07,987 --> 00:41:08,546
Sealed.

622
00:41:21,706 --> 00:41:22,387
Xiaoming,

623
00:41:24,827 --> 00:41:26,106
having a friend is really nice.

624
00:41:31,546 --> 00:41:32,907
Good that you know it.

625
00:41:41,706 --> 00:41:44,666
By the way, I have a gift for you.

626
00:41:47,026 --> 00:41:50,467
From now on, don't write your diary
on scrap paper page by page.

627
00:41:54,787 --> 00:41:56,026
You drew this?

628
00:41:57,026 --> 00:41:58,586
I am a tree traveling the world.

629
00:41:59,867 --> 00:42:01,467
Then this dove must be me.

630
00:42:02,307 --> 00:42:03,106
Yeah.

631
00:42:04,387 --> 00:42:05,467
Then let's write together.

632
00:42:06,026 --> 00:42:06,546
Okay.

633
00:42:07,307 --> 00:42:09,016
I'll write my part
and leave it with you.

634
00:42:09,626 --> 00:42:10,666
So she can't sneak a peek.

635
00:42:11,506 --> 00:42:12,827
That's perfect.

636
00:42:14,427 --> 00:42:16,586
We have our own diary now.

637
00:42:17,146 --> 00:42:19,907
We can share our secrets in writing.

638
00:42:20,987 --> 00:42:23,307
We have our own little world.

639
00:42:53,944 --> 00:42:58,313
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

640
00:42:59,867 --> 00:43:01,347
Ren Xiaoming betrayed our friendship.

641
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
